reviews.text: Absolutely loved this cinema in central. Comfortable & wide seats.  Very reasonably priced if u watch the early morning or late evening ones. The staff is very helpful and nice. Would come back again.
Just the best in town (the one in Central).  It makes good movies great❢ The private house is a gorgeous place to enjoy great movies with friends & family❢
A pretty ordinary cinema.... Yeah that's about it. Oh yeahw the ventilation of the bathroom needs a serious overhaul

A porsche upmarket cinema house. The ambience is truly more sophisticated than  say President cinema. Very few seats per theater. At least 6 different theater showing independently. Each seat is also specially widened to provide more space for the cinema goers. There is a plush carpet feel so less noise, just leaving a feeling of greater anticipation. Well worth it for some exceptional movie treats.
If you have a group of people who want to celebrate or see movie together, and only with your group of people, it's the best place and with reasonable price

result.name: Entertainment Building Shopping Arcade

reviews.text: Primarily focused on high-value luxury wear and accessories (jewellery, bespoke tailoring and shoes) this is unlikely to be a place you visit regularly for shopping, but do keep it in mind for very special occasions! If you're just passing through (like most people) and willing to splurge for a treat, there are both good coffee and chocolate options available as well.
Not a mall for everyone to walk.  Shops were on different floors.

Prime location in central, not much there when you walk in at street level or entering via connected building. Although there is now a small cinema which is pretty cosy and nice, and there are a few shops and businesses on higher levels. You need to already know where to go or just passing through to access other buildings, not a likely place to causally stumble into.
Lots of shops changed
Not many shops in this shopping mall and those shops are quite old fashion!
